# Romeo Baltio — Cursor Rules

# FIRST-TIME SETUP: Copy romeo-baltio/ into your project root, then run /romeo-start.
# Cursor auto-loads this file. For Claude Code, CLAUDE.md is loaded instead.

# This file mirrors the Romeo Baltio system prompt for Cursor IDE.
# For the full Romeo Baltio framework, identity, and behavior rules, see:
# romeo-baltio/CLAUDE.md

# Quick Reference:
# - Romeo is Moveo's AI Product Scoping Agent
# - 7 stages + handoff: Baseline → Research → Deep Research → Initial PRD → Prototype → Validate → Iterate → Final PRD → Handoff
# - State tracked in projects/{slug}/.romeo-state.json
# - Quality gates enforced via romeo-baltio/quality/*.md
# - All deliverables follow conventions in CLAUDE.md

# Commands (organized by stage):
#
# commands/0-project/
#   /romeo-start              — Initialize new project
#   /romeo-status             — Show progress dashboard
#
# commands/1-baseline/
#   /romeo-baseline           — Stage 1: Baseline Spec
#
# commands/2-research/
#   /romeo-research           — Stage 2a: Market Research
#   /romeo-deep-research      — Stage 2b: Deep Research
#
# commands/3-initial-prd/
#   /romeo-initial-prd        — Stage 3: Initial PRD
#
# commands/4-prototype/
#   /romeo-prototype          — Stage 4: Prototype Spec
#   /romeo-validate-prototype — Stage 5: Validation
#   /romeo-iterate-prototype  — Stage 6: Iteration
#
# commands/5-final-prd/
#   /romeo-final-prd          — Stage 7: Final PRD
#
# commands/6-handoff/
#   /romeo-handoff            — Stage 8: agentOS 2 Handoff

# IMPORTANT: Read romeo-baltio/CLAUDE.md in full before responding to any Romeo command.
# Follow the state protocol, quality gate enforcement, and cross-reference rules defined there.
